@d16 9
a24 9
A ranger instinctively knows the relationship of each of the
cardinal directions (of the compass) to each other.  He is able to
pinpoint true north to within (10 - Rank) degrees.  A ranger can
also estimate the distance he has travelled overland to within (90 +
Rank)\% accuracy.  The maximum amount of travel which can be
estimated by a ranger is (1 + Rank) consecutive weeks' worth (see
83.4).  A check must be made to determine the accuracy of the Ranger's
estimate each time he reaches his time limit.  Both the above rules
are exceptions to rule 48.4.
